A 14-year-old student, Franz Andersin, described the chaos during the shooting at a school in Finland.
The Finnish Prime Minister, Matti Vanhanen, labeled the incident as a "great tragedy."
The shooter, an 18-year-old student, targeted classmates and the headmistress, leaving a total of eight dead.
The shooter, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, had expressed admiration for Hitler and Stalin and posted videos online detailing his plans.
The shooting, the worst in Finnish history, has deeply shaken the sense of security in society.
The government has extended condolences and flags are flown at half-mast in remembrance
